HEADWORD: Pulsion
<hw>Pul"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulsio</ets>, fr. <ets>pellere</ets>, <ets>pulsum</ets>, to drive:
cf. F. <ets>pulsion</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of driving forward;
propulsion; -- opposed to <ant>suction</ant> or
<ant>traction</ant>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

